about.summary: Run VS Code on a remote server.

name: code-server
raw_recipe:
{% set name = "code-server" %}
{% set version = "4.5.2" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url: https://github.com/cdr/code-server/releases/download/v{{ version }}/code-server-{{ version }}-linux-amd64.tar.gz  # [linux64]
  sha256: 9de1d55afcd4793519e26a52a1f6efc9f5f3ac7a46680e8125d03e02a63e8d91  # [linux64]
  url: https://github.com/cdr/code-server/releases/download/v{{ version }}/code-server-{{ version }}-linux-arm64.tar.gz  # [aarch64]
  sha256: 1c0f4b3eaf99c1ba9d2bf87084fa64f9d1e3f64d5bc417226aeb446cafacc08e  # [aarch64]
  url: https://github.com/cdr/code-server/releases/download/v{{ version }}/code-server-{{ version }}-macos-amd64.tar.gz  # [osx]
  sha256: b61cf50e3dc1bd3f8b0b63c0ffb2f110ec23e167ef4ab69d0689b9b7b37b1831  # [osx]
  folder: code-server

build:
  number: 0
  binary_relocation: false  # [osx]
  skip: true  # [win or aarch64]

requirements:
  build:
    - sysroot_linux-64 2.17  # [linux64]
  host:
    - nodejs 16.*
  run:
    - nodejs 16.*

test:
  commands:
    - code-server --help

about:
  home: https://github.com/cdr/code-server
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file:
    - code-server/LICENSE
    - code-server/ThirdPartyNotices.txt
  summary: Run VS Code on a remote server.

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - xhochy
    - jtilly
    - janjagusch

about.summary: Run VS Code on a remote server.
